.Dd @MDOCDATE@
.Dt @PACKAGE_NAME@ \&1 "User Commands"
.Os @PACKAGE_STRING@
.Sh NAME
.Nm @PACKAGE@
.Nd advanced dynamic window manager for X
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Bl -item -compact
.It
.Nm
.Bk -words
.Op Ar OPTIONS
.Li [{ Ns Fl f Ns Li | Ns Fl -file Ns Li } Li [ Ns Ar PATH/ Ns Li ] Ns Ar RCFILE Ns Li ]
.Ek
.It
.Nm
.Bk -words
.Op Ar OPTIONS
.Li { Ns Fl h Ns Li | Ns Fl -help Ns Li }
.Ek
.Nm
.Bk -words
.Op Ar OPTIONS
.Li { Ns Fl v Ns Li | Ns Fl -version Ns Li }
.Ek
.It
.Nm
.Bk -words
.Op Ar OPTIONS
.Li { Ns Fl C Ns Li | Ns Fl -copying Ns Li }
.Ek
.El
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm @PACKAGE_NAME@
is a lightweight window manager for X inspired by
.Xr echinus 1 ,
.Xr spectrwm 1 
and
.Xr dwm 1 .
It manages windows in maximized, floating and tiled layouts.
Either layout can be applied dynamically, optimizing the environment for the
application in use and the task performed.
.Pp
In maximized layout only one window can be seen at the moment, but you
can switch between them with hotkeys.
In floating layout windows can be resized and moved freely.
Dialog windows are always managed floating, regardless of the layout applied.
.Pp
Windows are grouped by tags. Each window can be tagged with one or
multiple tags. Selecting certain tags displays all windows with these tags.
.Pp
.Nm @PACKAGE_NAME@
draws a small border around windows to indicate the focus state and an
optional title bar and resize grips.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Pp
The options that are detailed below are recognized by
.Nm .
.Nm
uses
.Xr getopt_long_only 3 ,
so unambiguous abbreviations of long options and long options with a
single dash are also supported.
.Ss COMMAND OPTIONS
.Pp
By default,
.Nm
will launch the window manager and search for the default named
configuration file,
.Pa @PACKAGE@rc ,
in the directories listed under section
.Sx FILES ,
below.
The following standard options change this behaviour:
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width "XX"
.It Fl h Ns Li , Ns Fl -help
Prints usage information to standard output, then exits.
.It Fl v Ns Li , Ns Fl -version
Prints version information to standard output, then exits.
The first word of the first line of output is consistent with previous
versions of
.Nm
and contains the string "@PACKAGE@-@VERSION@".  However, whereas
previous versions only output a single line, versions after 0.7.4 output
multiple lines.
.It Fl C Ns Li , Ns Fl -copying
Prints copying permissions to standard output, then exits.
.El
.Ss GENERAL OPTIONS
.Pp
The following non-standard options can also be supplied:
.Bl -tag -width "XX"
.It Fl f Ns Li , Ns Fl -file Li [ Ns Ar PATH/ Ns Li ] Ns Ar RCFILE
Specifies an alternative configuration file.
By default,
.Nm
loads the configuration file named
.Pa @PACKAGE@rc ,
searching the directories specified under
.Sx FILES ,
below.
When only a file name,
.Ar RCFILE ,
is specified as an argument, the same directories are searched for the
file named
.Ar RCFILE .
If a path to the file,
.Ar PATH ,
is also specified, the directory corresponding to
.Ar PATH
is prepended to the directory search list, and
.Ar RCFILE
is sought beginning with that directory.  This is so that
.Nm
is consistent with the implementation in previous versions, but includes
additional directories to search.
.It Fl D Ns Li , Ns Fl -debug Li [ Ns Ar LEVEL Ns Li ]
Print detailed diagnostic information to standard error during
operation.  Increases or sets the debugging level to
.Ar LEVEL .
This option can be repeated to further increase the debugging output.
The default level is zero (0).
.It Fl V Ns Li , Ns Fl -verbose Li [ Ns Ar LEVEL Ns Li ]
Print diagnostic information to standard output during operation.
Increases or sets the verbosity level to
.Ar LEVEL .
This option can be repeated to further increase the verbosity of output.
The default level is one (1).
.El
.Sh FEATURES
Following are some of the features provided by
.Nm @PACKAGE_NAME@
not provided by similar window managers:
.Pp
.Sy General:
.Pp
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
full NetWM/EWMH, WinWM/WMH (gnome), OSF/Motif and ICCCM 2.0 compliance;
.It
full support for ICCCM 2.0 client and global modality;
.It
full RANDR and Xinerama compliance with full support for multi-head setups;
.It
full support for Window Maker dock applications in floating and tiling modes;
.It
window manager based auto-hide for panels and docks (struts);
.It
three focus models: click-to-focus, sloppy and all-sloppy;
.It
soon to come X11R6 session management;
.It
very wide array of available key-binding actions;
.It
key-binding defaults consistent with a wide array of light-weight and popular window managers.
.El
.Pp
.Sy "Views, Workspaces and Desktops:"
.Pp
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
view/tag based workspaces and desktops;
.It
scroll wheel support for switching desktops;
.It
key bindings for switching desktops observes EMWH desktop layout.
.El
.Pp
.Sy "Floating/stacking mode:"
.Pp
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
smart cascading placement algorithm;
.It
window decorations: title bar, resize grips, wide array of configurable buttons.;
.It
themed buttons include hovered, toggled, pressed, focused and unfocused pixmaps.;
.It
multiple mouse actions per title bar button based on mouse button pressed.;
.It
separate click and click-drag actions for title bar, borders and grips.;
.It
windows can snap to other windows and workspace/monitor boundaries.;
.It
key bindings for moving and resizing windows without using the mouse.
.It
drop shadowed XFT text in title bars, with separate color selection for active, focused, inactive and unfocused windows;
.It
dragging of windows between monitor;
.It
.Xr metacity 1 -like
drag-to-left, -right or -top functions to optimize single-desktop operation.
.El
.Pp
.Sy "Tiling modes:"
.Pp
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
per-monitor tiling layouts for multi-head setups;
.It
multiple tiling layouts including master/stacking, monocle and grid (but, no dwindle or centered-master modes, yet);
.It
key bindings for rotating tiling layouts and also for rotating windows through tiling layouts;
.It
adjustable window borders and inter-window margins;
.It
one pixel open space around dynamic desktop area for clicking on the root window in tiled modes;
.It
ability to drag-and-swap windows in tiling layouts (ala
.Xr awesome 1 ,
.Xr wmii 1
and
.Xr spectrwm 1 Ns ).
.El
.Ss CONVENTIONS
.Pp
The following notation is used in this page:
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width "XX" -offset indent -compact
.It Ic A
Alt.
.It Ic C
Control.
.It Ic S
Shift.
.It Ic W
Windows key.
.It Ic M
Mod key (definable to one of the above).
.It Ic M1
Left mouse button.
.It Ic M2
Middle mouse button.
.It Ic M3
Right mouse button.
.It Ic M4
Scroll wheel up.
.It Ic M5
Scroll wheel down.
.El
.Ss MOUSE BINDINGS
.Pp
