.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Pp
When not terminated by a signal,
.Nm
will exit with one of the following exit statuses, indicating the
success or failure of the program.
.Bl -tag -width ".Li 127"
.It Li 0
.Li (EXIT_SUCCESS)
The program ran successfully and completed normally.
.It Li 1
.Li (EXIT_FAILURE)
The program failed due to an unrecoverable error and exited abnormally.
A diagnostic message is normally printed to standard error before exit.
.It Li 2
.Li (EXIT_SYNTAXERR)
The program detected a syntax error during option processing and exited.
A diagnostic message is normally printed to standard error before exit.
.It Li 127
The program could not execute and was not expecting to return from the
.Xr execve 3
instruction, and therefore, exited abnormally.
.El
