.Sh HISTORY
.Nm @PACKAGE_NAME@
began from adding EWMH/NetWM support to
.Xr echinus 1 ,
which was itself derived from
.Xr dwm 1 .
It soon became clear that to support some of the advanced features that
we intended would require a significant rewrite and
.Nm @PACKAGE_NAME@
was born out of that rewrite.
.Pp
I had been adding EWMH/NetWM 1.5 support to
.Xr blackbox 1 ,
.Xr icewm 1 ,
.Xr etwm 1 ,
and others such as
.Xr 2bwm 1 ,
and
.Xr echinus 1 .
What I was looking for was a nice light-weight window manager with
stacking and tiling support and advanced theme support and customization
that could be used as a primary and fallback window manager for the X
Desktop Environment and the unexicon Linux distribution.
Rather than rewrite an old one (like
.Xr blackbox 1 Ns ),
I started implementing all of the EWMH/NetWM support from scratch under
.Nm @PACKAGE_NAME@ .
